# Input Method & Layout Fix Plan

## Goal Description
Resolve the "Wayland Diagnose" warning regarding `GTK_IM_MODULE` and ensure the 'ç' character functions correctly on the user's keyboard layout.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The fix involves modifying environment variables and keyboard layout settings which might affect other input behaviors.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [envs.conf](file:///home/rob/.config/hypr/envs.conf)
- Remove or modify `GTK_IM_MODULE`.
- Ensure `QT_IM_MODULE` and others are set correctly for Wayland.

#### [MODIFY] [input.conf](file:///home/rob/.config/hypr/input.conf)
- Adjust `kb_layout` and `kb_variant` to ensure 'ç' support (likely `us-intl` or dedicated `br` layout).

### System
- Check [/etc/environment](file:///etc/environment) or shell profiles if variables persist outside Hyprland config (though Hyprland config is the primary suspect).

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- User to reload Hyprland.
- User to type 'ç' (usually `AltGr + ,` or `' + c` depending on layout).
- Verify warning no longer appears on boot.
